{"word":"H7843 - שָׁחַת - shâchath - shaw-khath' - Batter","slug":"H7843","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׁחַת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shâchath"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shaw-khath'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Batter"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D7;&#x05EA; - sha&#x0302;chath</b> - <i>shaw-khath'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>decay</i>, that is, (causatively) <i>ruin</i> (literally or figuratively): - batter, cast off, corrupt (-er, thing), destroy (-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, X utterly, waste (-r)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4889\">H4889</a>, <a href=\"#/H4892\">H4892</a>, <a href=\"#/H4893\">H4893</a>, <a href=\"#/H516\">H516</a>, <a href=\"#/H7848\">H7848</a>, <a href=\"#/H7851\">H7851</a>"}]}